n Code of Conduct","NHS Supply Chain Code of Conduct","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518799/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-18","Funerals: Costs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the findings of the recent British Medical Association report <i>In Good Hands: Tackling labour rights concerns in the manufacture of medical gloves</i>.","false","Biography information for Lord Crisp",,"Lord Crisp","HL93"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518800","Department of Health","false","2016-05-26","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence has produced guidance on faecal microbiota transplant for recurrent <em>Clostridium difficile</em> infection under the interventional procedure programme. This programme makes recommendations about the safety of the procedures and how well they work. However the guidance does not constitute a direction to National Health Service trusts to provide the interventions. Decisions about whether to provide a treatment are taken locally.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL97","2016-05-26T16:29:01.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518800/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518800/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518800/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-18","Prime Minister: Ministerial Policy Advisers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what action they are taking to ensure that NICE guidance is followed in the use of faecal microbiota transplants in the treatment of recurrent Clostridium difficile.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL94"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518801","Department of Health","false","2016-05-26","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) has produced guidance on faecal microbiota transplant for recurrent <em>Clostridium difficile</em> infection. NICE has recommended that the procedure is safe enough for use in the National Health Service, but no assessment of its cost effectiveness has been made by NICE.</p><p> </p><p>Data on the uptake by the NHS of faecal microbiota transplants in the treatment of recurrent <em>Clostridium difficile</em> is not collected centrally.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL96","2016-05-26T16:25:27.557Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518801/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518801/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518801/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-18","Prime Minister: Ministerial Policy Advisers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the outcome and cost effectiveness of the use of faecal microbiota transplants in the treatment of recurrent Clostridium difficile infections.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL95"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518802","Department of Health","false","2016-05-26","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) has produced guidance on faecal microbiota transplant for recurrent <em>Clostridium difficile</em> infection. NICE has recommended that the procedure is safe enough for use in the National Health Service, but no assessment of its cost effectiveness has been made by NICE.</p><p> </p><p>Data on the uptake by the NHS of faecal microbiota transplants in the treatment of recurrent <em>Clostridium difficile</em> is not collected centrally.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL95","2016-05-26T16:25:27.73Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518802/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518802/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518802/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-18","Burial and Cremation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the rate of uptake by the NHS of faecal microbiota transplants in the treatment of recurrent Clostridium difficile infections.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL96"
