"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518929","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-24","<p>The UK is not currently involved in active treaty discussions with Tanzania.</p><p> </p><p>Discussions with Malawi over a new tax treaty began some years ago, and substantive agreement has been reached at official level. The Government of Malawi have stated that they hope to be in a position to sign the new treaty in the near future.</p><p> </p><p>The UK has negotiated a treaty with Lesotho and are currently seeking to arrange signature.</p><p> </p><p>The UK is currently involved in negotiations with Ghana in agreeing a new tax treaty.</p><p> </p><p>Nepal has approached the UK to begin negotiation of a tax treaty. We are seeking suitable dates for discussions.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","37145 ; 37146","2016-05-24T14:07:46.973Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518929/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518929/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518929/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-18","Taxation: Tanzania","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether HM Revenue and Customs is in discussions with Tanzania about a tax treaty between the UK and Tanzania.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","37144"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518930","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-24","<p>The UK is not currently involved in active treaty discussions with Tanzania.</p><p> </p><p>Discussions with Malawi over a new tax treaty began some years ago, and substantive agreement has been reached at official level. The Government of Malawi have stated that they hope to be in a position to sign the new treaty in the near future.</p><p> </p><p>The UK has negotiated a treaty with Lesotho and are currently seeking to arrange signature.</p><p> </p><p>The UK is currently involved in negotiations with Ghana in agreeing a new tax treaty.</p><p> </p><p>Nepal has approached the UK to begin negotiation of a tax treaty. We are seeking suitable dates for discussions.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","37144 ; 37146","2016-05-24T14:07:47.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518930/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518930/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518930/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-18","Taxation: Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what progress has been made in updating tax treaties between the UK and (a) Malawi, (b) Lesotho and (c) Ghana.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","37145"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518931","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-24","<p>The UK is not currently involved in active treaty discussions with Tanzania.</p><p> </p><p>Discussions with Malawi over a new tax treaty began some years ago, and substantive agreement has been reached at official level. The Government of Malawi have stated that they hope to be in a position to sign the new treaty in the near future.</p><p> </p><p>The UK has negotiated a treaty with Lesotho and are currently seeking to arrange signature.</p><p> </p><p>The UK is currently involved in negotiations with Ghana in agreeing a new tax treaty.</p><p> </p><p>Nepal has approached the UK to begin negotiation of a tax treaty. We are seeking suitable dates for discussions.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","37144 ; 37145","2016-05-24T14:07:47.1Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518931/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518931/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518931/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-18","Taxation: Nepal","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what progress has been made in negotiating a tax treaty between the UK and Nepal.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","37146"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518932","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-23","<p>Tax-advantaged employee share schemes are greatly valued by both companies and employers, and the government wants to make sure that the rules surrounding these schemes are as simple and clear as possible. Budget 2016 made a number of changes to the rules for employment-related securities and options which will make these schemes fairer and easier for taxpayers to understand, and therefore encourage businesses to use them.</p><p> </p><p>An HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) commissioned report conducted by Oxera considered the effect of the tax-advantaged employee share schemes on productivity. The report is available at: http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20110203095056/http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/research/tax-advantaged-report2.pdf.</p><p> </p><p>The government’s most recent assessment of the cost of the tax-advantaged employee share schemes to the Exchequer is provided in the table below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Forecast cost of Income Tax relief (2015-16)</p></td><td><p>Forecast cost of National Insurance relief (2015-16)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Share Incentive Plan</p></td><td><p>£220 million</p></td><td><p>£165 million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Save As You Earn</p></td><td><p>£180 million</p></td><td><p>£140 million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Enterprise Management Incentives</p></td><td><p>£70 million</p></td><td><p>£40 million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Company Share Option Plan</p></td><td><p>£70 million</p></td><td><p>£40 million</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>HMRC has not withdrawn the valuation checking service for the tax-advantaged employee share schemes. However, HMRC has withdrawn other checks for non-tax advantaged schemes as, in the majority of cases, acceptable valuations were submitted. Therefore, the valuation service added no value and is seen as unnecessary.</p><p> </p><p>The government keeps all areas of the tax system under review and as part of that in always interested in understanding the views of all interested parties.</p><p> </p><p>Treasury Ministers and officials have meetings with a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery. Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations on departmental business are published on a quarterly basis and are available at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","37283 ; 37284 ; 37285","2016-05-23T15:55:04.05Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518932/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518932/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518932/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-18","Revenue and Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what meetings (a) he and (b) Ministers of his Department have had with officials of his Department in which withdrawal of the valuation check service by HM Revenue and Customs was discussed since May 2015; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","37117"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518933","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-24","<p>The Lifetime ISA is a complement to the existing pension system. It will provide savers with greater choice and flexibility in how they save for retirement.</p><p> </p><p>From April 2017, people aged 18 to 40 will be able to save up to £4,000 each year into a Lifetime ISA and receive a 25% bonus from the Government.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-05-24T14:06:46.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518933/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518933/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518933/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-18","Individual Savings Accounts: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on levels of pension saving of the introduction of the lifetime ISA.","false","Biography information for Ian Blackford","Ross, Skye and Lochaber","Ian Blackford","37150"
