"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518940","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-24","<p>HM Revenue and Customs does not have details of the number of people engaged in employment through an employment intermediary. Employment intermediaries are required to deduct tax and National Insurance contributions from most people engaged in employment and tax returns are monitored, but no count is kept of the total numbers of workers.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-05-24T13:55:46.047Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518940/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518940/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518940/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-18","Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what information HM Revenue and Customs holds on the number of people engaged in employment through an employment intermediary in each year since 2008.","false","Biography information for Rob Marris","Wolverhampton South West","Rob Marris","37181"
