"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519049","Department for Education","false","2016-05-23","<p>The total pre-opening revenue expenditure for free school projects that opened or were withdrawn or cancelled in 2011 to 2015 is published on GOV.UK at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/523706/Free_Schools_Data_for_Publication.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/523706/Free_Schools_Data_for_Publication.xlsx</a></p><p>The capital costs of all free school projects, including any costs incurred on projects that have withdrawn, are included in the Department for Education’s annual accounts which are published on GOV.UK at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dfe-annual-reports" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dfe-annual-reports</a></p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-05-23T16:22:17.593Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519049/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519049/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519049/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-18","Free Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much was spent on free school projects that did not result in the establishment of a school in each year since 2011.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","37381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519050","Department for Education","false","2016-05-26","<p>As at 23 May 2016, 110 free schools were in some form of temporary accommodation. Some of these schools will be open in temporary accommodation on their permanent site as part of a phased transition.</p><p> </p><p>Opening free schools in temporary accommodation has ensured that we have been able to meet a need for places and support free school trusts to open much needed new schools at the earliest opportunity.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-05-26T16:39:31.78Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519050/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519050/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519050/answer","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519050/answer/previousversion/226","Biography information for Edward Timpson","60","Education","Education","2016-05-18","Free Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many free schools are in temporary accommodation.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","37382"
