"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519264","Department of Health","false","2016-05-24","<p>In 2015, figures showed smoking prevalence rates in adults and 15 year olds in England to be at 18% and 8% respectively. The most recent quarterly information on prevalence of smoking among pregnant women, published in March, show this to be 10.6%.</p><p>Smoking prevalence is at its lowest ever level with official figures showing that the Government met each of the targets set out in its Tobacco Control Plan – Healthy Lives, Healthy People. A new Tobacco Control Plan is currently being developed.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","37408 ; 37409","2016-05-24T13:09:18.487Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519264/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519264/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519264/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-18","Smoking: Pregnancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate his Department has made of the prevalence of smoking among pregnant women.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","37418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519265","Department of Health","false","2016-05-24","<p>NHS England has advised that it expects to publish information on Cancer Drugs Fund (CDF) expenditure for 2015-16 in Board Papers for NHS England’s Board meeting on 26 May 2016.</p><p>The budget allocated for the CDF for 2015-16 was £340 million and new financial control mechanisms, to be put in place from 1 July 2016, are intended to ensure that the CDF does not exceed its fixed £340 million budget in 2016-17.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-05-24T09:49:28.833Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519265/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519265/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519265/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-18","Cancer: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much was spent by the Cancer Drugs Fund in 2015-16; and how much that fund is estimated to spend in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","37420"
